cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with semantic segmentation of remote sensing images using Convolutional Networks. The paper also proposes a novel technique to perform multi-scale segmentation without increasing the number of parameters, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of dilated networks and the evaluation of the proposed algorithm on remote sensing datasets could also make it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) category as it deals with image processing and analysis.
